<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10096b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10096b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10096b"> 96(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Monsieur, fr&egrave;re du roi</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Jusqu&apos;&agrave; la mort du cardinal <font color="green">[Richelieu]</font>, il <font color="green">[Pierre d&apos;Alm&eacute;ras]</font> fut un des membres de cette camarilla, tri&eacute;e avec tant de pr&eacute;cautions, et dont faisaient partie le comte de Rochefort, Bouthillier de Chavigny, Du Tremblay (si c&eacute;l&egrave;bre sous le nom de P&egrave;re Joseph), la duchesse d&apos;Aiguillon, etc. C&apos;&eacute;tait le Conseil, plus ou moins secret, charg&eacute; de d&eacute;fendre le ministre contre la triple coterie de la reine m&egrave;re, de la reine et de <mark>Monsieur, fr&egrave;re du roi</mark>. [Until the death of Cardinal Richelieu, Pierre d&apos;Alm&eacute;ras was one of the members of this coterie that had been selected with much care. The group included the Count of Rochefort, Bouthillier de Chavigny, Du Tremblay (famous under the name Father Joseph), the Duchess of Aiguillon, etc. This was the more-or-less secret Council that was assigned to defend the minister against the triple coterie of the Queen Mother, the Queen, and Monsieur, Brother to the King. <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 163</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
